# ============================================================================
# App Store Connect API Credentials
# ============================================================================
#
# This file is a TEMPLATE. Copy it to .env and fill in your actual credentials.
#
# IMPORTANT: DO NOT COMMIT the actual .env file to git!
# The .env file should be in .gitignore to keep your credentials secure.
#
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ASC_KEY_ID - App Store Connect API Key ID
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This is the Key ID shown in App Store Connect when you create an API key.
#
# How to obtain:
# 1. Log into App Store Connect: https://appstoreconnect.apple.com
# 2. Navigate to: Users and Access → Keys → App Store Connect API
# 3. Click "Generate API Key" (requires Account Holder or Admin role)
# 4. Give it a name (e.g., "Fastlane Automation")
# 5. Select "App Manager" or higher access level
# 6. The Key ID is shown in the format: ABC12DEF34
#
# Example: ASC_KEY_ID=ABC12DEF34
ASC_KEY_ID=YOUR_KEY_ID_HERE

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ASC_ISSUER_ID - App Store Connect Issuer ID
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This is your organization's Issuer ID, shown on the API Keys page.
# It's a UUID that identifies your App Store Connect organization.
#
# How to obtain:
# 1. Log into App Store Connect: https://appstoreconnect.apple.com
# 2. Navigate to: Users and Access → Keys
# 3. Look for "Issuer ID" at the top of the page
# 4. It's a UUID in the format: 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
#
# Example: ASC_ISSUER_ID=12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
ASC_ISSUER_ID=YOUR_ISSUER_ID_HERE

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ASC_KEY_BASE64 - App Store Connect API Key (Base64 encoded)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This is your .p8 private key file, base64-encoded for secure storage.
#
# SECURITY NOTE: This key grants API access to your App Store Connect account.
# Keep it secure and never commit it to version control.
#
# How to obtain:
# 1. When you create the API key in App Store Connect, click "Download API Key"
# 2. Download the .p8 file (named AuthKey_XXXXXXXXXX.p8)
# 3. IMPORTANT: You can only download this file ONCE. Store it securely!
# 4. Convert it to base64 using this command:
#
#    base64 -i ~/Downloads/AuthKey_XXXXXXXXXX.p8 | tr -d '\n'
#
#    (Replace XXXXXXXXXX with your actual Key ID)
#
# 5. Copy the entire base64 output and paste it below
#
# The base64 string will be very long (around 200 characters).
#
# Example: ASC_KEY_BASE64=LS0tLS1CRUdJTiBQUklWQVRFIEtFWS0tLS0tCk1JR1RBZ0VBTUJNR0J5cUdTTTQ5...
ASC_KEY_BASE64=YOUR_BASE64_ENCODED_KEY_HERE

# ============================================================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this template to create your .env file:
#    cp fastlane/.env.template fastlane/.env
#
# 2. Fill in the three values above with your actual credentials
#
# 3. Verify .env is in .gitignore:
#    grep -q "fastlane/.env" .gitignore || echo "fastlane/.env" >> .gitignore
#
# 4. Test your credentials:
#    bundle exec fastlane ios asc_dry_run
#
# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# If you get authentication errors:
#
# 1. Verify the Key ID matches the one in App Store Connect
# 2. Verify the Issuer ID is correct (it's the same for all keys)
# 3. Ensure the base64 encoding has no line breaks (use tr -d '\n')
# 4. Check that the API key has sufficient permissions (App Manager or higher)
# 5. Verify the key hasn't been revoked in App Store Connect
#
# If you need to regenerate:
#
# 1. Go to App Store Connect → Users and Access → Keys
# 2. Revoke the old key
# 3. Generate a new key
# 4. Download the new .p8 file immediately
# 5. Update all three values in this .env file
#
# ============================================================================
# FOR CI/CD (GitHub Actions)
# ============================================================================
#
# For GitHub Actions, these credentials are stored as repository secrets:
#
# 1. Go to your repository on GitHub
# 2. Navigate to: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# 3. Create three repository secrets:
#    - ASC_KEY_ID (paste the Key ID)
#    - ASC_ISSUER_ID (paste the Issuer ID)
#    - ASC_KEY_BASE64 (paste the base64-encoded key)
#
# The GitHub workflow will automatically use these secrets.
# You do NOT need to commit the .env file for CI/CD to work.
